@startuml AdriaBOX_Download_Sequence
!theme plain
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

title AdriaBOX - File Download Sequence (Zoom Level 1)

actor "Client (CLI)" as client
participant "Metadata Server" as server
database "SQLite DB" as db
participant "Storage Node A" as nodeA
participant "Storage Node B" as nodeB

== Metadata Request Phase (REST API) ==

client -> server : 1. GET /api/download/{filename}
activate server

server -> db : 2. Lookup file chunks & locations
activate db
db --> server : 3. Allocation Map (Chunk1->NodeA, Chunk2->NodeB)
deactivate db

server --> client : 4. 200 OK (Returns Allocation Map)
deactivate server

== Data Fetching Phase (TCP Sockets) ==

client -> nodeA : 5. TCP Connect & Request Chunk 1
activate nodeA
nodeA -> nodeA : 6. Read from Docker Volume
nodeA --> client : 7. Send Chunk 1 (Binary Data)
deactivate nodeA

client -> nodeB : 8. TCP Connect & Request Chunk 2
activate nodeB
nodeB -> nodeB : 9. Read from Docker Volume
nodeB --> client : 10. Send Chunk 2 (Binary Data)
deactivate nodeB

== Finalization ==

client -> client : 11. Reassemble chunks into original file

@enduml
